Removing Twitter Handles (@user)¶

In [ ]:
def remove_pattern(text, pattern):
  r = re.findall(pattern, text)

  for i in r:
    text = re.sub(i,"",text)

  return text
In [ ]:
combine["Tiddy Tweet"] = np.vectorize(remove_pattern)(combine['tweet'], "@[\w]*")

def Hashtags_Extract(x):
  hashtags=[]

  for i in x:
    ht = re.findall(r'#(\w+)',i)
    hashtags.append(ht)

  return hashtags
